Write a function that reverses a string. The input string is given as an array of characters s.
You must do this by modifying the input array in-place with O(1) extra memory.
Solution:
var reverseString = function(s) {
let left = 0;
let right = s.length - 1; while (left < right) {
// swapping
let temp = s[left];
s[left] = s[right];
s[right] = temp;
left++;
right--;
}
return s;
};
Explanation:
s = [“h”, “e”, “l”, “l”, “o”]
Initially:
left = 0
right =s.length-1=5-1=4
left<right(0<4)//true goes inside the while loop
temp=s[0]//h
s[left]=s[4]//o
s[right]=temp//h
left++;//1
right--;//3Iteration 2:
left=1
right=3
left<right(1<3)
temp=s[1]//e
s[left]=s[3]//l
s[right]=temp//e
left++;//2
right--;//2
2<2(as condition is false) it comes out of loop.It returns the output
output:s=[“o”,”l”,”l”,”e”,”h”].reverse of a string
Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)
